{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"afa7259c-2722-4154-b23b-f5e8cd5980d7","content":"Here are the issues I found:\n\n1. **Missing `identity`** (line 1) — Required field for .NET templates is absent.\n\n2. **`shortName: \"restore\"`** (line 5) — Conflicts with the built-in `dotnet restore` command.\n\n3. **`defaultValue: \"net7.0\"`** (line 10) — Not in the defined choices (`net8.0`, `net9.0`). Default must be a valid choice.\n\n4. **`defaultValue: \"yes\"`** (line 19) — Bool datatype expects `\"true\"` or `\"false\"`, not `\"yes\"`.\n\n5. **`defaultValue: \"abc\"`** (line 24) — Not a valid integer for an `int` datatype.\n\n6. **`computed1` missing `value`** (line 26) — Computed symbols require a `value` expression.\n\n7. **`generated1` missing `generator`** (line 29) — Generated symbols require a `generator` property.\n\n8. **Post action missing `actionId`** (line 34) — Each post action needs an `actionId` GUID to identify the action type.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"efb66ef8-8d2f-423b-a4f4-de132f58bcd7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me analyze the template.json for issues:\n\n1. **Missing required fields**: The `identity` field is required in .NET template.json but is missing. Also `sourceName` is commonly expected.\n\n2. **`shortName: \"restore\"`**: This is a reserved/common short name used by dotnet CLI. Using \"restore\" could conflict with `dotnet restore`.\n\n3. **`defaultValue: \"net7.0\"` for `targetFramework`**: The default value is \"net7.0\" but that's not one of the available choices (which are \"net8.0\" and \"net9.0\"). The default must be one of the defined choices.\n\n\n4. **`enableLogging` has a non-standard default**: For a boolean parameter, the default should be \"true\" or \"false\", not \"yes\".\n\n5. **`maxRetries` has an invalid default**: The default value \"abc\" isn't a valid integer.\n\n6. **`computed1` is missing its expression**: Computed symbols need a `value` property to define what they calculate.\n\n7. **`generated1` is missing its generator**: Generated symbols require a `generator` property to specify how they're created.\n\n8. **`postActions` entry is incomplete**: One of the post-action entries is missing the `action` property.","outputTokens":617,"requestId":"A7C5:1007E7:1349C03:159C6C3:6A027B63"},"id":"f1569f0b-69c6-4e25-864b-850d1c898377","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:59:27.990Z","parentId":"cac5a4ca-30db-4aae-9e06-1dee7eb12f29"}
